reviewText:
My complaint is simple - this is a bad port.

Playing this game without a controller is all but impossible. If you have a controller, it's ok, but still it doesn't have much of what you would expect of a good game on PC. Also a big disappointment for me was lack of voice acting. Maybe it's characteristic for LEGO games in general, I don't know (I bought this one for my kid only because it was Harry Potter), but here you are:

- not playable without a controller;
- no voice acting;
- more than a few liberties taken with the plot and the universe of HP.

If you are ok with all of the above, go ahead and get it. It does have a fair share of content. But try to get it at a discount.
